00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.790
when he ran over those-- that young lady

263
00:18:44.860 --> 00:18:46.860
that was trying to go to work.

264
00:18:46.930 --> 00:18:48.240
What was he thinking?

265
00:18:52.550 --> 00:18:56.130
- I'm one of the 12 jury that sat through this trial.

266
00:18:56.200 --> 00:19:00.340
The moment I walked in there and I realized.

267
00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:04.410
when the case started. how intense it was gonna be.

268
00:19:04.480 --> 00:19:07.720
I started thinking. should I be on this case?

269
00:19:07.790 --> 00:19:11.000
But I knew I had a duty to perform.

270
00:19:12.510 --> 00:19:14.720
- Now what you're gonna learn during the course

271
00:19:14.790 --> 00:19:16.790
of this trial. ladies and gentlemen.

272
00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:22.410
is that Ms. Ruiz and Ms. Melton had three things in common.

273
00:19:24.370 --> 00:19:30.100
Both of them died on the 7th of October. 2019.

274
00:19:31.580 --> 00:19:35.480
Both of them had been strangled.

275
00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:41.410
And both of them. the last person that they encountered

276
00:19:41.480 --> 00:19:43.620
was Mr. Wade Wilson.

277
00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:45.130
- He was smirking.

278
00:19:45.200 --> 00:19:47.510
He was staring jurors down.

279
00:19:47.580 --> 00:19:51.270
When we were picking a jury. we had a juror cry.

280
00:19:51.340 --> 00:19:52.890
There were jurors that were terrified

281
00:19:52.960 --> 00:19:55.890
just being in the courtroom near him

282
00:19:55.960 --> 00:19:57.340
that we had to excuse.

283
00:19:57.410 --> 00:20:00.240
- He made a lot of eye contact.

284
00:20:00.310 --> 00:20:02.930
especially when we were walking in.

285
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:06.000
And for me. he would look directly at me at times.

286
00:20:06.060 --> 00:20:08.270
and that stuck with me as well.

287
00:20:10.340 --> 00:20:12.750
- Now. ladies and gentlemen. during the course

288
00:20:12.820 --> 00:20:14.340
of this trial. you're gonna hear

289
00:20:14.410 --> 00:20:16.650
about all of the admissions that he made.

290
00:20:16.720 --> 00:20:22.270
You're gonna hear what he told law enforcement.

291
00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:26.370
And you're gonna hear that when they asked him

292
00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:30.100
why he killed Ms. Melton. he said.

293
00:20:30.170 --> 00:20:31.790
I just wanted to do it.

294
00:20:44.030 --> 00:20:45.060
- And then...

295
00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:50.960
They asked him. well. what about Ms. Ruiz?

296
00:20:53.310 --> 00:20:56.100
His response was...

297
00:21:00.200 --> 00:21:03.310
"Eff it.

298
00:21:03.370 --> 00:21:05.820
"I should kill her.

299
00:21:05.890 --> 00:21:07.370
I already got one down."

300
00:21:18.030 --> 00:21:23.650
- When you take all of that and you put it together.

301
00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:28.000
the State wants you to return the only verdict that

302
00:21:28.060 --> 00:21:32.270
the evidence is gonna support. and that is guilty

303
00:21:32.340 --> 00:21:36.030
of first-degree premeditated murder for the strangulation

304
00:21:36.100 --> 00:21:39.480
and killing of Ms. Melton.

305
00:21:39.550 --> 00:21:44.650
guilty for battery on Ms. Melissa Montanez.

306
00:21:44.720 --> 00:21:50.960
guilty on first-degree murder of Ms. Diana Ruiz

307
00:21:51.030 --> 00:21:54.240
for strangling. killing her.

308
00:21:54.310 --> 00:21:57.930
and running her over with that car.

309
00:21:59.790 --> 00:22:02.000
- I was trying to still keep an open mind.

310
00:22:02.060 --> 00:22:05.440
I was battling my mind and my heart at the same time for--

311
00:22:05.510 --> 00:22:07.790
for days. weeks.

312
00:22:12.860 --> 00:22:15.550
- There's only so much you can do with this case.

313
00:22:15.620 --> 00:22:17.370
Usually when you do an opening.

314
00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:20.790
you like to have a solid defense

315
00:22:20.860 --> 00:22:22.790
or something in your favor.

316
00:22:25.170 --> 00:22:28.130
And at that point. we were still

317
00:22:28.200 --> 00:22:31.550
tiptoeing through the tulips. trying to come up with one.

318
00:22:33.510 --> 00:22:35.960
The defense is gonna-- is gonna reserve. judge.

319
00:22:36.030 --> 00:22:37.200
- Okay.

320
00:22:37.270 --> 00:22:39.000
Very well.

321
00:22:39.060 --> 00:22:40.790
- For a defense attorney to then say.

322
00:22:40.860 --> 00:22:42.580
uh. we waive our opening statement.

323
00:22:42.650 --> 00:22:43.930
and then the judge looks at the State and says.

324
00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:46.340
okay. call your first witness. it's like. whoa.

325
00:22:47.750 --> 00:22:50.060
- The State calls Melissa Montanez.

326
00:22:52.960 --> 00:22:54.580
- You went from being the love of his life

327
00:22:54.650 --> 00:22:55.960
to testifying against him.

328
00:22:56.030 --> 00:22:57.130
Like. that's gotta be hard.

329
00:23:14.370 --> 00:23:18.200
- I honestly did not think I was gonna be able to do it.

330
00:23:21.130 --> 00:23:24.270
- I begged and pleaded that I didn't want to.

331
00:23:24.340 --> 00:23:25.960
You're saying I have to sit in front of him...

332
00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:32.130
- And you're saying I have to testify against him in court.

333
00:23:32.200 --> 00:23:33.750
I couldn't do it.

334
00:23:33.820 --> 00:23:37.680
It wasn't until they told me how important

335
00:23:37.750 --> 00:23:39.680
that it was that I--I was.

336
00:23:39.750 --> 00:23:43.550
Like. I was the only voice for Kristine Melton and Diane Ruiz.

337
00:23:48.200 --> 00:23:52.030
- Because I was the only one that he beat up and survived...

338
00:23:54.960 --> 00:23:59.750
- That I could say. then. how scary he was.

339
00:24:01.170 --> 00:24:02.620
- Do you solemnly swear or affirm

340
00:24:02.680 --> 00:24:03.790
that the testimony that you give

341
00:24:03.860 --> 00:24:05.310
will be the truth. the whole truth.

342
00:24:05.370 --> 00:24:06.410
and nothing but the truth?

343
00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:07.550
- Yes.

344
00:24:09.310 --> 00:24:12.060
I don't know if it'll ever really set in.

345
00:24:12.130 --> 00:24:16.550
It's just surreal to be able to absorb that

346
00:24:16.620 --> 00:24:19.620
somebody you were in love with killed two women.

347
00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:21.790
was a serial killer. I guess.

348
00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:27.060
- Weirdly enough. I could understand if he murdered me.

349
00:24:28.620 --> 00:24:32.170
But I can't imagine him just randomly

350
00:24:32.240 --> 00:24:34.960
going on a killing spree for girls he did not know.

351
00:24:35.030 --> 00:24:38.960
It feels--like. I have a lot of guilt on that.

352
00:24:39.030 --> 00:24:41.270
- Now. do you know someone by the name of Wade Wilson?

353
00:24:41.340 --> 00:24:42.620
- Yes.

354
00:24:42.680 --> 00:24:44.550
- Did you date him for a short period of time?

355
00:24:44.620 --> 00:24:46.060
- Yes.

356
00:24:46.130 --> 00:24:47.170
Yes.

357
00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:48.790
I was hyperventilating.

358
00:24:48.860 --> 00:24:52.200
I couldn't get my breath in. thought I was gonna pass out.

359
00:24:54.130 --> 00:24:56.930
I had cried many different times before getting in there.

360
00:24:57.000 --> 00:24:59.100
ruined my makeup several different times.

361
00:24:59.170 --> 00:25:01.550
ruined my hair several different times.

362
00:25:01.620 --> 00:25:03.820
just trying to get in there.

363
00:25:03.890 --> 00:25:07.000
- And then she described in gruesome detail...

364
00:25:09.030 --> 00:25:13.480
What her interaction was when she had met him up at her spa.

365
00:25:13.550 --> 00:25:15.580
And. you know. the--

366
00:25:15.650 --> 00:25:18.820
the pain and suffering that she had to endure at his hands

367
00:25:18.890 --> 00:25:22.340
was unimaginable.

368
00:25:22.410 --> 00:25:24.270
- How did he act?

369
00:25:24.340 --> 00:25:26.340
- Violent. aggressive.

370
00:25:26.410 --> 00:25:28.100
I knew I was gonna die that day.

371
00:25:28.170 --> 00:25:30.270
I was just buy--buying time.

372
00:25:30.340 --> 00:25:33.370
I'm trying to reason with him. trying to talk to him.

373
00:25:33.440 --> 00:25:35.680
But there's nobody behind those eyes anymore.

374
00:25:35.750 --> 00:25:41.960
- Okay. so at some point. does he--

375
00:25:42.030 --> 00:25:44.440
does he continue to beat you as you're up there?

376
00:25:44.510 --> 00:25:45.720
- Yes. - Does he punch you?

377
00:25:45.790 --> 00:25:46.720
- Yes.

378
00:25:46.790 --> 00:25:48.480
- Okay. describe that punch.

379
00:25:48.550 --> 00:25:52.790
- The final and end punch that I remember.

380
00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:55.410
he got me so straight on.

381
00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:59.410
and blood just went crazy. everywhere.

382
00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:04.890
And it almost was like. a minute where I could dunk under

383
00:26:04.960 --> 00:26:08.930
and run under his arm. run down the stairs.

384
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.240
and then that's when my neighboring businesses.

385
00:26:11.310 --> 00:26:13.720
the design studio. were calling me--

386
00:26:13.790 --> 00:26:15.620
Mila. Mila. get--get in here.

387
00:26:15.680 --> 00:26:18.930
And then. like. I didn't even realize how crazy I looked.

388
00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:21.030
but like. they rescued me.

389
00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:22.510
And I don't know what happened after that.

390
00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:24.000
I'm assuming he left.

391
00:26:26.790 --> 00:26:30.100
- Having a child of my own or a daughter.

392
00:26:30.170 --> 00:26:32.550
no man wants to see their kid go through that.

393
00:26:32.620 --> 00:26:34.790
Of course. you would sympathize with her.

394
00:26:34.860 --> 00:26:37.650
I'm just happy that she made it out alive.

395
00:26:37.720 --> 00:26:40.170
- Now. do you. as you're sitting here in court.

396
00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:42.130
see the person who has threatened to kill you.

397
00:26:42.200 --> 00:26:44.510
and who was battering you that morning. sitting in court?

398
00:26:44.580 --> 00:26:45.820
- Yes.

399
00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:47.930
- Would you please point to him and identify him

400
00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:48.930
by his clothing?

401
00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:51.890
- Wade Wilson in the blue suit.

402
00:26:51.960 --> 00:26:54.000
- Gonna let the record reflect that the witness

403
00:26:54.060 --> 00:26:56.750
has identified the defendant.

404
00:26:56.820 --> 00:27:02.100
To testify against him and to see his face again.

405
00:27:02.170 --> 00:27:03.960
that's a really. really hard thing

406
00:27:04.030 --> 00:27:05.650
for witnesses to have to do.

407
00:27:05.720 --> 00:27:10.410
She's strong to come in and testify and strong to--

408
00:27:10.480 --> 00:27:12.890
to be able to stand up on cross.

409
00:27:12.960 --> 00:27:14.240
- When you were at the Buddha Bar.

410
00:27:14.310 --> 00:27:16.310
or before going to the Buddha Bar...

411
00:27:19.060 --> 00:27:21.890
- Did you-- were you using cocaine?

412
00:27:21.960 --> 00:27:23.620
- Yes.

413
00:27:23.680 --> 00:27:24.960
- Your cocaine?

414
00:27:25.030 --> 00:27:26.060
- No.

415
00:27:26.130 --> 00:27:27.060
- Who's?

416
00:27:27.130 --> 00:27:29.030
- He--he had some.

417
00:27:30.820 --> 00:27:33.550
- You said-- when you met up with him.

418
00:27:33.620 --> 00:27:37.240
you said there was nobody behind those eyes anymore.

419
00:27:37.310 --> 00:27:38.240
- Yes. that's true.

420
00:27:38.310 --> 00:27:39.680
- What did you mean?

421
00:27:39.750 --> 00:27:42.060
- Dark. serial-killer eyes.

422
00:27:42.130 --> 00:27:44.060
where there's nothing to reason with.

423
00:27:44.130 --> 00:27:45.410
It's a black hole.

424
00:27:45.480 --> 00:27:46.890
You're saying words.

425
00:27:46.960 --> 00:27:49.060
You're trying to evoke emotion in somebody.

426
00:27:49.130 --> 00:27:53.100
and there's nothing behind those eyes.

427
00:27:53.170 --> 00:27:55.410
- Nothing further. Judge.

428
00:27:55.480 --> 00:27:57.440
- She withstood cross-examination

429
00:27:57.510 --> 00:28:00.310
like a palm tree in a hurricane. I'll tell you that.

430
00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.130
- Any redirect? - Nothing further.

431
00:28:02.200 --> 00:28:04.200
I ask that she be released. - Any objection?

432
00:28:04.270 --> 00:28:05.860
- No. - She can be excused.

433
00:28:05.930 --> 00:28:08.000
You're--you can step down. You're excused.

434
00:28:09.750 --> 00:28:11.410
- I don't--I can't think of anything I've done.

435
00:28:11.480 --> 00:28:13.720
harder than that.

436
00:28:13.790 --> 00:28:17.240
And then I started getting all these death threats

437
00:28:17.310 --> 00:28:21.000
that I had testified against him.

438
00:28:21.060 --> 00:28:25.620
I couldn't show up to work for several months after the trial.

439
00:28:25.680 --> 00:28:28.100
I thought I did my job on trial.

440
00:28:28.170 --> 00:28:30.750
I thought that was all I had to speak.

441
00:28:30.820 --> 00:28:35.240
I didn't know I had to further defend myself after all this.

442
00:28:35.310 --> 00:28:38.410
and I didn't know that there was. I don't know.

443
00:28:38.480 --> 00:28:41.240
hundreds of thousands of girls

444
00:28:41.310 --> 00:28:43.480
that I had to defend myself from.

445
00:28:43.550 --> 00:28:44.750
from a serial killer.

446
00:28:44.820 --> 00:28:46.100
That was crazy.

447
00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:49.890
- We call them the Wade Wives.

448
00:28:49.960 --> 00:28:51.750
I think they call themselves Wade Wives.

449
00:28:51.820 --> 00:28:55.620
people who were trying to have relationships with him.

450
00:28:55.680 --> 00:28:58.240
- He did ask for pictures.

451
00:28:58.310 --> 00:29:00.960
And then when he got them. he was like. obviously

452
00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:04.370
very sweet. very charming. and complimentary

453
00:29:04.440 --> 00:29:05.680
about the pictures.

454
00:29:05.750 --> 00:29:08.060
And then he was asking for more.

455
00:29:08.130 --> 00:29:13.440
- This defendant. who's covered with facial tattoos.

456
00:29:13.510 --> 00:29:15.960
and for some reason. fascinates people...

457
00:29:16.030 --> 00:29:18.410
- Meet Wade Wilson. who apparently has been

458
00:29:18.480 --> 00:29:20.860
taking over corners of TikTok.

459
00:29:20.930 --> 00:29:22.270
- Wade Wilson. - Wade Wilson.

460
00:29:22.340 --> 00:29:24.860
- He's charismatic and he has. like. tattoos.

461
00:29:24.930 --> 00:29:26.620
- He knew what was going on on the outside.

462
00:29:26.680 --> 00:29:28.820
He knew what was being posted on TikTok.

463
00:29:28.890 --> 00:29:31.620
He literally knows everything.

464
00:29:31.680 --> 00:29:34.030
- And then it certainly didn't help that his name

465
00:29:34.100 --> 00:29:36.510
is Wade Wilson from "Deadpool."

466
00:29:36.580 --> 00:29:38.240
- We can fight this.

467
00:29:40.200 --> 00:29:42.370
- I'm sure you've been seeing him all over your

468
00:29:42.440 --> 00:29:45.790
For You page. Wade Wilson. the Deadpool killer.

469
00:29:45.860 --> 00:29:48.170
- He really thinks that he's a Marvel character?

470
00:29:49.680 --> 00:29:51.650
- It kind of reminds you of Charles Manson

471
00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:52.960
a little bit. doesn't it?

472
00:29:53.030 --> 00:29:55.240
He was building a cult following.

473
00:29:55.310 --> 00:29:56.960
There were women. and there were folks out there

474
00:29:57.030 --> 00:29:59.410
that were actually following his--his commands

475
00:29:59.480 --> 00:30:01.580
and--and getting tattoos done.

476
00:30:03.550 --> 00:30:05.100
- I did.

477
00:30:05.170 --> 00:30:07.310
I have it right here.

478
00:30:10.240 --> 00:30:12.650
It was one of those. tattoo your name on me

479
00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:13.650
so I know it's real.

480
00:30:15.820 --> 00:30:19.000
Sorry. but it was. literally the words from his mouth.

481
00:30:20.370 --> 00:30:21.890
And I've never done that before.

482
00:30:21.960 --> 00:30:23.650
I don't have any other name on my body. including my children.

483
00:30:23.720 --> 00:30:25.720
So it was a big-- it was something

484
00:30:25.790 --> 00:30:28.310
that I was very serious about.

485
00:30:34.030 --> 00:30:36.480
- I mean. again. I think he's a master manipulator.

486
00:30:36.550 --> 00:30:38.270
so he knows how to get what he wants.

487
00:30:45.000 --> 00:30:46.790
- So inmates are entitled to having

488
00:30:46.860 --> 00:30:49.480
what's called a canteen or a money account

489
00:30:49.550 --> 00:30:52.370
to purchase items. purchase food. what have you.

490
00:31:06.820 --> 00:31:08.440
- He had girls all around the world

491
00:31:08.510 --> 00:31:10.720
writing him. sending him money.

492
00:31:10.790 --> 00:31:13.890
He had more canteen than he can even use.

493
00:31:13.960 --> 00:31:18.030
that even guys were fangirling over him.

494
00:31:48.130 --> 00:31:50.860
- In the four or five years that Wade Wilson was in jail.

495
00:31:50.930 --> 00:31:54.650
we saw Wade Wilson go through a series of women

496
00:31:54.720 --> 00:31:56.510
who were absolutely enthralled with him.

497
00:31:56.580 --> 00:31:58.370
I'm Dr. Casey Jordan.

498
00:31:58.440 --> 00:32:01.510
I'm a criminologist. attorney. and behavior analyst.

499
00:32:01.580 --> 00:32:06.170
There's a sense of safety and control in loving a bad boy.

500
00:32:06.240 --> 00:32:08.410
Look. here's a violent person.

501
00:32:08.480 --> 00:32:11.410
I'm controlling him. and he can't hurt me.

502
00:32:11.480 --> 00:32:13.310
It's not just his good looks. though.

503
00:32:13.370 --> 00:32:16.370
It's the notoriety of his horrific crimes.

504
00:32:18.370 --> 00:32:19.820
- Morning.

505
00:32:19.890 --> 00:32:21.510
- Please introduce yourself to the ladies and gentlemen

506
00:32:21.580 --> 00:32:22.860
of the jury by telling them your name.

507
00:32:22.930 --> 00:32:25.580
- Sure. how you doing? I am Doctor Thomas Coyne.

508
00:32:25.650 --> 00:32:29.170
I was the deputy chief medical examiner here at District 21.

509
00:32:29.240 --> 00:32:31.890
- Did you have an opportunity to perform

510
00:32:31.960 --> 00:32:34.340
an autopsy of Ms. Diana Ruiz?

511
00:32:34.410 --> 00:32:36.130
- I did.

512
00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:38.890
So these are all photographs that were taken

513
00:32:38.960 --> 00:32:41.030
on the day of the autopsy in the morgue.

514
00:32:41.100 --> 00:32:43.000
here in Fort Myers.

515
00:32:43.060 --> 00:32:45.650
- I always take note of--of how the defendant

516
00:32:45.720 --> 00:32:47.720
responds to certain evidence.

517
00:32:47.790 --> 00:32:51.060
And Wade Wilson stared right at those autopsy photos.

518
00:32:51.130 --> 00:32:53.650
almost as if he was proud of what he did.

519
00:32:53.720 --> 00:32:58.440
In Wade Wilson's cell. he has photos on the wall.

520
00:32:58.510 --> 00:33:01.270
For him. it's a brag sheet.

521
00:33:01.340 --> 00:33:03.580
The most disturbing photo is the field

522
00:33:03.650 --> 00:33:06.370
